   {:e #blake3 "40ee058835464a20c68c2c509a967fd6e4ce337ac70291bef0ea66b05d450877" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Tasks untouched for 5+ sessions accumulate and dilute R(t). Need a decay mechanism. APPROACH: (1) Add :task/last-session-touched (Instant, One) attribute to schema in schema.rs. (2) On any task interaction (show, go, close, update), record current session timestamp via transact. (3) In methodology_gaps() or harvest, scan for tasks where last-session-touched is greater than 5 sessions stale AND priority less than P4. (4) Auto-downgrade to P4 with retraction+assertion of :task/priority. (5) Report in braid status: 'N tasks auto-decayed to backlog'. (6) Manual priority override persists — decay only applies if no explicit interaction in the window. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After 5 sessions without touching task X, X.priority == P4. (B) Task decay count appears in status output. (C) Manually setting priority resets the decay timer. (D) P0 tasks are exempt from decay (critical work should never auto-decay). CONSIDERATIONS: The session count threshold (5) should be a config datom, not hardcoded. This allows tuning. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/task.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance/methodology.rs" :op :assert}
